Text: What we've done this weekWe had one team meeting with Jeremiah and did the presentation on Friday as well as sneaking in some last minute features to our UI.
Over the last week we worked on some labelling features and refined the superpixel merging process.

What went wellWe did a good job in the last week of really prioritising what we needed to to do and stuck to these priorities without being swayed too much by the multiple directions we could have taken.
We were also well organised with getting the presentation done and everyone got their parts done quickly.
Overall, our team did well over the course of the project to take charge of tasks and improve on things each week.
Everyone has contributed well to the project and we would not have had the final product without everyone's contributions.
I've also noticed that Rara's technical skills have improved a lot since the first time I worked with her and it is fun to see people improve as the year has gone by.
Jeremiah also seemed pleased with the work we had, although it would have been nice to produce something that was a bit more complete for him.
Things to improve as a teamI felt that in the last week, the enthusiasm to get a lot of work done was not as high from some team members andÂ  I felt they had already moved on from the project.
I was a little concerned with this because I felt we still needed to work hard on the project even it was only a few days until we would be done.

This might have been due to not have some clear goals for the week, so next time it might be worth looking into another way to keep team members aware of what our goals were to make sure we are on the same page.
Things I could do betterI felt I could have done a better job making everyone feel like they were included in the project.
There may have been times where my habit of digging into peoples ideas to try understand them, might have come across a bit too critical, which I will need to make sure to work on in the future.
I felt that I may have made them feel as if their ideas were being shut down too quickly without being heard.
Next time I will try to be a bit more open minded and more encouraging when discussing ideas.
I also feel my personal attachment to the project led to some weird perceptions of how hard each person should work in the project.
Although I never expressed this to anyone, there were times where I felt the amount of work being done by some team members was not enough in certain periods of time.
I feel that I need to be more aware of the expectations of the hours per week on the project (20), and that I should not expect other people to be in the same mindset as myself.
Goals for next week and beyondThe main goal for the coming week is to get the portfolio done and then hopefully do prep work for the internship coming up.
General ThoughtsThe project has been great in terms of learning more amount image processing and creating a machine learning interface.
Although there were plenty of things I could have done better over the project, I felt I gave my best effort in the project and worked hard to try deliver a great product as a team.
There have been some hard time with some teammates but I'm optimistic that any issues will start to be resolved with a bit of distance from the stress of the work we were going through.
The biggest lesson this project has taught me is that no matter how hard you try or how well you plan for things, there will always be issues.
These issues might be unexpected personality clashes or technical issues that you were never aware of.

It feels like when when we face these unexpected obstacles, it's important to not panic or complain - but to attack the issue as best you can and not worry if the path changes from where you thought it would end up.
